# Public Methods First

When organizing class methods:

- Place publicly exposed methods first.
- Place internal/private helpers (for example names starting with `_`) after all public methods.
- Keep behavior unchanged when doing this reordering; it is a structure-only refactor.

Example:

```python
class Example:
    def public_api(self) -> None:
        ...

    def _internal_helper(self) -> None:
        ...
```
